    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I pay Colombian taxes on my foreign income?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          No, not initially. As a non-resident for tax purposes (first 183 days), you're only taxed on Colombian-source income. After 4 years of residency, you may become a tax resident. Consult a tax professional for your situation.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I renew the Digital Nomad Visa?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. The visa can be renewed for additional 2-year periods. Start the renewal process 2-3 months before expiry to avoid gaps.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Colombia safe for digital nomads?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Generally yes, in tourist and expat areas. Medellín, Bogotá's nice neighborhoods, and coastal tourist towns are safe with normal precautions. Avoid isolated areas at night, don't flash valuables, use Uber/inDrive instead of street taxis.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the digital nomad community like?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Large and active, especially in Medellín. Coworking spaces (Selina, WeWork, local spots), weekly meetups, Facebook groups, and plenty of other nomads. It's one of the world's most established nomad scenes.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I open a Colombian bank account?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes, with your Cédula de Extranjería. Bancolombia and Davivienda are nomad-friendly. You'll need your cédula, passport, and sometimes proof of income. Digital banks like Nequi work with just a passport initially.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How's the internet in Colombia?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Excellent in major cities. Medellín has reliable fiber connections (100+ Mbps common). Coworking spaces and cafes have solid backup connections. Rural and some coastal areas may have issues.
        </p>
      </div>
